---
title: "BuzzLLM — Tool Execution Cycle (L3)"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant llm as invoke_llm
    participant registry as ToolRegistry
    participant tool as Tool impl
    participant subprocess as rg or find
    participant ddg as DuckDuckGo
    participant brave as Brave API
    participant docker as Docker daemon
    participant container as pyexec container

    Note over llm: LLM response contained tool_calls

    llm->>registry: run_tools(tool_calls, registry)

    par concurrent tool execution
        registry->>tool: execute(args) — e.g. BashRipgrep
        tool->>subprocess: tokio::process::Command (timeout 30s)
        subprocess-->>tool: stdout lines
        tool->>tool: validate_path + paginate_results
        tool-->>registry: JSON result

    and
        registry->>tool: execute(args) — e.g. SearchWeb
        tool->>ddg: GET lite.duckduckgo.com (reqwest)
        alt DDG success
            ddg-->>tool: HTML response
            tool->>tool: parse with scraper crate
        else DDG bot detection or failure
            tool->>brave: GET api.search.brave.com
            brave-->>tool: JSON results
        end
        tool-->>registry: JSON array of results

    and
        registry->>tool: execute(args) — e.g. PythonExecute
        tool->>docker: create + start container (bollard)
        docker-->>tool: container running on localhost:port
        tool->>container: TCP send JSON code
        container-->>tool: JSON stdout + stderr + result
        tool->>tool: truncate if over 10000 chars
        tool-->>registry: JSON result
    end

    registry-->>llm: all results collected

    llm->>llm: print tool results as StreamResponse(ToolResult)
    llm->>llm: assemble_tool_messages into conversation
    Note over llm: loop back to POST next LLM request
